<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-35-0261 </DOCNO><TEXT>A treatment of the discipline of atmospheric chemistry. Beginning withthe fundamentals of kinetics and photochemistry, it shows how the experimentaltechniques in these areas are applied to the study and control of chemicalreactions in the troposphere. There is detailed analysis of such majorsocietal issues as smog, acid rain, and volatile toxic organics. Theseven criteria pollutants considered by the U.S. Environmental ProtectionAgency to be hazardous are examined. Over 340 illustrations.</TEXT></DOC>